    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-04T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-04T05:00:00-05:00" n="526"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d526">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4A6/372: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-04T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 4, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 4—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Department’s 15, July 3, 3 p.m. Conference may include in an annex to new
                    convention the parts of the Geneva Convention referred to in my 34, July 2, 10
                    a.m., with necessary alterations.</p>
                <p>Delegation finds none of the ideas contained in these chapters of the convention
                    inimical to our interests after minor alterations are made. The delegation
                    however does not feel competent to make recommendation as to questions of policy
                    involving signature to a convention leaving certain action to the Council of the
                    League of Nations such as provided in articles 8, 9, 10, 19, and 20 and more
                    especially the sanctions provided for in article 24. Conference yesterday
                    adopted following article: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The High Contracting Parties shall communicate to one another through
                            the Secretary General of the League of Nations the laws and regulations
                            promulgated in order to give effect to the present convention and shall
                            forward to the Secretary General of the League of Nations an annual
                            report on the working of the convention in their territories in
                            accordance with a form drawn up by the Advisory Committee on Traffic in
                            Opium and Other Dangerous Drugs of the <pb facs="0777" n="663"
                                xml:id="pg_663"/> League of Nations and approved by the Council of
                            the League of Nations”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Delegation sees no objection to accepting this but abstained from voting and
                    reserved position pending receipt of instructions from Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
